properties.desc: You step inside the crypt room and see a crypt surrounded by everblooming flowers - the ultimate sign of respect in Risan.
You see a lot of unmarked graves in this room.
You enter the room and see that someone recently lived here.
You look around the room and see many dug-up graves.
You enter the room and see many broken tombstones littering the ground. It seems the assaulter injured himself in the process.
You see many graves scattered about the room with no discerning pattern, probably done in a rush.
You see many tombstones in this room, weathered to various stages of brokenness.
You look up, and see hay falling through the ceiling.
You sneeze at the large quantity of hay in the room.
You step inside the room and see piles of blood everywhere.
You look around and see many dead flowers littering the room. Somehow, one survived.
You step inside the fenced area and see numerous graves bearing no particular resemblance to one another.
You see a room clearly designed for entertainment purposes.
You see a building that was once designated for holy purposes.
You see a building designated for storing wood.
You see a room that was once lived in, seemingly recently.
You see many scattered furs about the ground.
The room here has torn scrolls, books, and destroyed potions everywhere.
You see a building designated for storing hay.
You see a building designated for storing flour.
You see a service building, where clients would be handled by service workers. They didn't seem to escape in time.
You see a few coffins strewn about the room.
You see many bird eggs and nests. This could possibly have been bird training, but the stench of blood in the air suggests otherwise.
You see a building designated for storing barrels.
You see a building designated for storing equipment.
You enter the room and see an odd arrangement, where people watch portals for fun.
You see many beds here, suggesting many people lived in this room.
You see a graveyard filled with many dead citizens. The nearby stream runs through the graveyard.
You feel an overwhelming sense of dread as you walk down the hallway.
You see a regal hallway, upkept despite its age.
You enter a storage room, containing various supplies to keep torture victims alive as long as possible.
You see tortuous implements in the room, with a large quantity of blood suggesting their extended use.
You see what looks like a very basic prison cell.
You see what looks like a very basic prison cell.
You see a strange statue as you enter the room, its gaze following you.
You see here a throne room. The throne blocked off by broken debris.
You see here a break room, filled with fun pass-time activities.
You see here a storage room, filled with hay and flour.
You see here a room filled with pillows. You wonder why there are so many.
You see here a room lined with gear, made to allow guards to mobilize in the fastest way possible.
You see a suspicious grave that has been recently moved around.
You find yourself in a carved-out enclave, filled with signs of life.
